sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Customer
    participant S as Sales Team
    participant F as Finance
    participant IT as IT Ops

    C->>S: Submit onboarding request
    S->>F: Credit check request

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION - Risk assessment and expedited path
    F->>F: Risk Assessment (Score >750, Verified Co., Clean History?)

    alt Low-Risk (all criteria met) — Expedited Path
        F-->>S: Auto-approved (low-risk, no director approval needed)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts (expedited)
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials (within 24h)
    else High-Risk — Standard Path
        F->>F: Escalate to Finance Director
        F-->>S: Finance Director Approval (24h SLA)
        S->>IT: Provision accounts
        IT-->>C: Welcome email + credentials
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

    C->>IT: First login confirmation
    IT->>S: Onboarding complete
    S->>C: Kickoff meeting scheduled

%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added a risk assessment step within Finance after the credit check request. Introduced an alt/else block: low-risk customers (score >750, verified company, clean payment history) receive automatic approval and proceed directly to expedited account provisioning, while high-risk customers are escalated to the Finance Director for manual approval before provisioning, preserving the original control flow. All existing post-provisioning steps (first login, onboarding complete, kickoff) remain shared across both paths.